citation: Proclamation under the Occupational Licensing Act 2005 (Tas)
text:
Proclamation under the Occupational Licensing Act 2005

I, the Governor in and over the State of Tasmania and its Dependencies in the Commonwealth of Australia, acting with the advice of the Executive Council, by this my proclamation made under section 2 of the Occupational Licensing Act 2005 fix 15 December 2010 as the day on which the following provisions of that Act commence:

        (a) sections 7(1A) and (1B) , 104(2) and (3) , 106(1) and 107 ;
        (b) Parts 2 and 3 of Schedule 2 ;
        (c) Parts 2 and 3 of Schedule 5 ;
        (d) Part 1 of Schedule 6 .
6 December 2010

PETER G. UNDERWOOD

Governor

By His Excellency's Command,

D. J. O'BYRNE

Minister for Workplace Relations

Displayed and numbered in accordance with the Rules Publication Act 1953.

Notified in the Gazette on 15 December 2010

This proclamation is administered in the Department of Justice.
